</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="fa764c21-9159-4390-aba9-565449e23645">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 16</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Three finger flick left: press Shift+Tab.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="df58ef38-3bae-4b1e-b668-04aef53283ee">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 17</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Three finger flick down (object mode): read current window.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="8f563b0c-046b-4922-a73d-e0eeea850ca1">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 18</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Three finger double tap: cycles through speech symbol levels which determine what symbols are spoken.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="04e3b943-2d05-4ce0-85b9-6fbc1e082c67">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 19</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Three finger triple tap: toggles screen curtain.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="1789bf49-9408-4459-bff1-2247608b9874">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 20</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Four finger tap: cycles through audio ducking modes.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="ead73b0a-5e4a-4aeb-a8b1-b9de50394867">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 21</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Four finger double tap: toggle input help mode.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="230e1353-315f-43a7-96b5-b2c060a4eda4">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 22</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Four finger flick left: report object with focus.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="972bf470-342c-430f-956b-e27cd23f1044">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 23</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Four finger flick right: report current navigator object.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="eefae056-3f75-4da9-8a71-db58592d2ebe">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 24</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Four finger flick up: report title of the current window.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="69bcc9c2-48fb-4615-a147-6f35ecd18ead">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 25</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Four finger flick down: report status bar text.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="312f9362-b26f-41b5-be6d-9d8a8e3dc253">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 27</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Touch browse mode</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="1e374318-c3c2-4326-97d8-16043a0fd94f">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 29</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>This touch mode, available in browse mode, allows you to navigate the document by selected element. This mode is entered automatically when browse mode becomes active, including switching to a browse mode document. From this mode, flicking up or down with one finger cycles through available element navigation modes, while flicking right or left with one finger moves to next or previous chosen element, respectively. Once you move away from browse mode documents or switch to focus mode, object touch mode will be used.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="01b3e7f1-de3c-4d48-b6d5-19fa889bbec6">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 31</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Available touch browse mode elements can vary between NVDA versionns. For NVDA 2025.3.3 and 2026.1, the available elements are default (move through elements/objects regardless of type), headings, tables, links, form fields, lists, frames, graphics, landmarks, embedded objects (dialogs and web apps, for example), and text paragraphs. In NVDA 2026.2, the available elements by default are default, headings, tables, links, form fields, and lists, with additional elements selectable from browse mode NVDA settings category.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="78fc5f20-4bd1-482f-a23e-1fb6c55d5b1e">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 33</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Note: this feature is included in NVDA 2026.2.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="a70a6c1e-1110-4408-9786-98a2de477bfd">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 35</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Synth settings touch mode</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="5989e396-17cc-4b52-9995-fcbe21122205">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 37</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>You can use this mode to quickly change synthesizer settings such as choosing a voice and changing volume. In this mode, use two finger flick left or right to move between synth settings and use two finger flick up and down gestures to change values. This gestures mirrors that of synth settings ring commands on the keyboard.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="7281a5e8-a0ae-405c-8f5d-d1382290473c">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 39</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>For a list of changes made between each add-on releases, refer to [changelogs for add-on releases][1] document.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
